#Installation

###Node, NPM packges and Grunt CLI

Download and install [Node JS](http://nodejs.org/download/).

*If you are on the Foxtel network, update the NPM proxy configuration:*

```
npm config set registry http://registry.npmjs.org/
npm config set proxy http://192.168.100.218:3128/
npm config set https-proxy http://192.168.100.218:3128/ 
``` 
 
Install dependencies with `npm install`

Install Grunt CLI globally: `npm install -g grunt-cli`
  
---

#Development

###Build Tasks

In the Terminal (Mac) or the Node Command Prompt (Windows), cd to the project directory.

From here you can run the following grunt tasks.

| Task              | Description
|-------------------|------------
|`grunt`            | Lint & Minify JavaScript, Compile Less
|`grunt server`     | Create Server + LiveReload
|`grunt dist`       | Create Distribution Build

